						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in Taḷavārike-hakkalu near the temple of Rāmaliṅga</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagattuṅga—(Undated).</p>						

						<p>This inscription referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Jagattuṅga,</hi> records the death of <hi rend="bold">Baḻiya Rēcha-gāmuṇḍa</hi> during the destruction of <hi rend="bold">Saṁgavūru,</hi> when <hi rend="bold">[Da]ntiga</hi> was governing the <hi rend="italic">nāḍu.</hi> <hi rend="bold">Gāmile,</hi> probably his wife, erected the memorial. The characters belong to <hi rend="bold">9th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
